# FuturesBot Project Issue Management

All issues for this repository must be created in the **FuturesBot** project in Linear.

**Project URL**: [https://linear.app/ericdahl/project/futuresbot-c639185ec497/overview](https://linear.app/ericdahl/project/futuresbot-c639185ec497/overview)

## Issue Creation Requirements

- **Project**: Always assign issues to the "FuturesBot" project
- **Team**: Always assign to the "FUT" team
- **Labels**: Apply relevant labels like "bug", "feature", "enhancement", "trading", "risk", etc.
- **Priority**: Set appropriate priority levels (0=No priority, 1=Urgent, 2=High, 3=Normal, 4=Low)

## When Creating Issues

- Use the MCP Linear tools to create issues directly in the FuturesBot project
- Navigate to the [FuturesBot project](https://linear.app/ericdahl/project/futuresbot-c639185ec497/overview) for project overview and issue management
- Ensure proper categorization and assignment
- Link related issues when applicable
- Include relevant context from the codebase

## Project Context

This repository contains a Coinbase futures trading bot implementation. All development work, bug reports, and feature requests should be tracked in the centralized FuturesBot project for proper project management and visibility.

## Example Issue Creation

```ruby
# When creating issues via MCP Linear:
mcp_Linear_create_issue(
  title: "Implement risk management controls",
  description: "Add position sizing and stop-loss logic",
  team: "FUT",
  project: "FuturesBot",
  labels: ["feature", "risk", "trading"],
  priority: 2
)
```
